node.text: Have you ever tried to make anything from concrete? As for me?...Let’s just say that cement and I would not have been seat mates on the school bus. I have had lots of successes with cement but if you leave with one tip of the day from this diy...know that you should NEVER use “cement all” quick set when trying to shove cement into pantyhose and tie it up with rubber bands unless you work like a cheetah sprinting while on steroids. The Pinterest girls made it looks so easy. 🤔 I did actually have 3 that turned out...one even being out of the “cement all”. 😱I guess I might be part cheetah. #diyconcrete #concretepumpkin #diygonewrong

node.text: After six years of stripping, sanding, and crack picking, it’s finished! What do you think?! Are you surprised that I decided to use the old knobs? Did you think I would end up painting it? Since it won’t fit through any of our doors to get it inside, we are just going to hang out here in our new outdoor living room and sniff the mountain air while listening to the neighbor dogs. I couldn’t be happier with the way that it turned out and I’m so excited to use this in our new kitchen when we build for towels, utensils, and all the things! Oh and if you ever paint any cabinets blue, I will come for you. Oh, and I love you! 😘 #mapcabinet #printerscabinet #drawers #ididit
